        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 5:01PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Keenesburg to over Log Lane
Village, or extending from 25 miles southeast of Greeley to near
Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Kersey, Keenesburg, Wiggins, Log Lane Village,
Orchard, Goodrich, Jackson Reservoir, Riverside Reservoir,
Weldona, Roggen, Adena School, Antelope Springs, Gill, Masters,
Fort Morgan Airport and Hardin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

If on Jackson or Riverside Reservoirs or other area lakes, get out
of the water and secure loose items. Boaters can expect strong gusty
winds and locally higher waves. Boaters should seek safe harbor
immediately.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
